    //
    // LOADING SCREENS
    //
    "clocktower.hint_1.title": "Dear evil, target the trusted",
    "clocktower.hint_1.header": "Eliminate players who are trusted by town.",
    "clocktower.hint_1.body": "A trusted or proven player who makes it to the end of the game will not get any votes. Choose your final three wisely.",
    "clocktower.hint_2.title": "Death is not the end in Blood on the Clocktower...",
    "clocktower.hint_2.header": "Dead players are still part of the game.",
    "clocktower.hint_2.body": "Do your best not to discount them. Sometimes they can have game-solving information!",
    "clocktower.hint_3.title": "Know your role... or the role you are bluffing",
    "clocktower.hint_3.header": "The Storyteller will not lie to you about rules.",
    "clocktower.hint_3.body": "If you have questions about your character or interactions, ask the Storyteller privately or publicly. Know how to use your information or how to lie about it.",
    "clocktower.hint_4.title": "Keep an eye on the votes",
    "clocktower.hint_4.header": "Pay attention to when people vote and who they vote on.",
    "clocktower.hint_4.body": "While it is essential for a Butler to pay attention to voting, all characters can gather information about who players trust or distrust based on their voting habits.",
    "clocktower.hint_5.title": "Don't take it personally...",
    "clocktower.hint_5.header": "Sometimes the best thing you can do for your team is die.",
    "clocktower.hint_5.body": "A Townsfolk nominating a Virgin, a Minion falling on their sword for their Demon, or an Imp choosing themselves to die can all benefit their respective teams.",
    "clocktower.hint_6.title": "Anyone can claim anything",
    "clocktower.hint_6.header": "Characters that are required to claim publicly can be bluffed by anyone.",
    "clocktower.hint_6.body": "In Trouble Brewing, anyone can claim to be the Slayer and \"shoot\" another player.",
    "clocktower.hint_7.title": "Advice on the Wiki",
    "clocktower.hint_7.header": "The wiki offers valuable advice for every character.",
    "clocktower.hint_7.body": "Whether you are the character, or bluffing as it, the wiki has tips and tricks you can use to guide your actions.",
    "clocktower.hint_8.title": "Kill with grace\nDie with dignity",
    "clocktower.hint_8.header": "Always remember: it's just a game.",
    "clocktower.hint_8.body": "Players are only playing the token they draw. Laugh, learn, and then rack up another game.",
    "clocktower.hint_9.title": "Misregistration Mayhem",
    "clocktower.hint_9.header": "Certain characters can be seen as other characters.",
    "clocktower.hint_9.body": "The Recluse *can* register as Evil or an Evil character and the Spy *can* register as Good or a Good character. It is up to the Storyteller if that happens and does not need to be consistent.",
    "clocktower.hint_10.title": "Final Four",
    "clocktower.hint_10.header": "Be careful who you execute, *if* you execute.",
    "clocktower.hint_10.body": "If you execute the wrong player when just four players live, the Demon only has to successfully kill one player to win the game.",
    "clocktower.hint_11.title": "Executions are necessary for Good to win",
    "clocktower.hint_11.header": "Good will not win if they do not execute.",
    "clocktower.hint_11.body": "Every executed player is decided by the votes of town, rather than chosen by the Demon.",
    "clocktower.hint_12.title": "One of a kind",
    "clocktower.hint_12.header": "Each character can only be in the game once.",
    "clocktower.hint_12.body": "Different characters have incentive to lie about themselves to trick the Evil Team. Although three people may be claiming Ravenkeeper, there cannot be more than one.",
