    //
    // ROLE DESCRIPTIONS
    //
    "clocktower.role.scapegoat.desc": "If a player of your alignment is executed, you might be executed instead.",
    "clocktower.role.gunslinger.desc": "Each day, after the 1st vote has been tallied, you may choose a player that voted: they die.",
    "clocktower.role.beggar.desc": "You must use a vote token to vote. If a dead player gives you theirs, you learn their alignment. You are sober & healthy.",
    "clocktower.role.bureaucrat.desc": "Each night, choose a player (not yourself): their vote counts as 3 votes tomorrow.",
    "clocktower.role.thief.desc": "Each night, choose a player (not yourself): their vote counts negatively tomorrow.",
    "clocktower.role.butcher.desc": "Each day, after the 1st execution, you may nominate again.",
    "clocktower.role.bonecollector.desc": "Once per game, at night*, choose a dead player: they regain their ability until dusk.",
    "clocktower.role.harlot.desc": "Each night*, choose a living player: if they agree, you learn their character, but you both might die.",
    "clocktower.role.barista.desc": "Each night, until dusk, 1) a player becomes sober, healthy & gets true info, or 2) their ability works twice. They learn which.",
    "clocktower.role.deviant.desc": "If you were funny today, you cannot die by exile.",
    "clocktower.role.apprentice.desc": "On your 1st night, you gain a Townsfolk ability (if good), or a Minion ability (if evil).",
    "clocktower.role.matron.desc": "Each day, you may choose up to 3 sets of 2 players to swap seats. Players may not leave their seats to talk in private.",
    "clocktower.role.voudon.desc": "Only you & the dead can vote. They don't need a vote token to do so. A 50 percent majority isn't required.",
    "clocktower.role.judge.desc": "Once per game, if another player nominated, you may choose to force the current execution to pass or fail.",
    "clocktower.role.bishop.desc": "Only the Storyteller can nominate. At least 1 opposing player must be nominated each day.",
    "clocktower.role.cacklejack.desc": "Each day, choose a player: a different player changes character tonight.",
    "clocktower.role.gangster.desc": "Once per day, you may choose to kill an alive neighbor, if your other alive neighbor agrees.",
    "clocktower.role.gnome.desc": "All players start knowing a player of your alignment. You may choose to kill anyone who nominates them.",
    "clocktower.role.washerwoman.desc": "You start knowing that 1 of 2 players is a particular Townsfolk.",
    "clocktower.role.librarian.desc": "You start knowing that 1 of 2 players is a particular Outsider. (Or that zero are in play.)",
    "clocktower.role.investigator.desc": "You start knowing that 1 of 2 players is a particular Minion.",
    "clocktower.role.chef.desc": "You start knowing how many pairs of evil players there are.",
    "clocktower.role.empath.desc": "Each night, you learn how many of your 2 alive neighbors are evil.",
    "clocktower.role.fortuneteller.desc": "Each night, choose 2 players: you learn if either is a Demon. There is a good player that registers as a Demon to you.",
    "clocktower.role.undertaker.desc": "Each night*, you learn which character died by execution today.",
    "clocktower.role.monk.desc": "Each night*, choose a player (not yourself): they are safe from the Demon tonight.",
    "clocktower.role.ravenkeeper.desc": "If you die at night, you are woken to choose a player: you learn their character.",
    "clocktower.role.virgin.desc": "The 1st time you are nominated, if the nominator is a Townsfolk, they are executed immediately.",
    "clocktower.role.slayer.desc": "Once per game, during the day, publicly choose a player: if they are the Demon, they die.",
    "clocktower.role.soldier.desc": "You are safe from the Demon.",
    "clocktower.role.mayor.desc": "If only 3 players live & no execution occurs, your team wins. If you die at night, another player might die instead.",
    "clocktower.role.clockmaker.desc": "You start knowing how many steps from the Demon to its nearest Minion.",
    "clocktower.role.dreamer.desc": "Each night, choose a player (not yourself or Travellers): you learn 1 good & 1 evil character, 1 of which is correct.",
    "clocktower.role.snakecharmer.desc": "Each night, choose an alive player: a chosen Demon swaps characters & alignments with you & then is poisoned.",
    "clocktower.role.mathematician.desc": "Each night, you learn how many players' abilities worked abnormally (since dawn) due to another character's ability.",
    "clocktower.role.flowergirl.desc": "Each night*, you learn if a Demon voted today.",
    "clocktower.role.towncrier.desc": "Each night*, you learn if a Minion nominated today.",
    "clocktower.role.oracle.desc": "Each night*, you learn how many dead players are evil.",
    "clocktower.role.savant.desc": "Each day, you may visit the Storyteller to learn 2 things in private: 1 is true & 1 is false.",
    "clocktower.role.seamstress.desc": "Once per game, at night, choose 2 players (not yourself): you learn if they are the same alignment.",
    "clocktower.role.philosopher.desc": "Once per game, at night, choose a good character: gain that ability. If this character is in play, they are drunk.",
    "clocktower.role.artist.desc": "Once per game, during the day, privately ask the Storyteller any yes/no question.",
    "clocktower.role.juggler.desc": "On your 1st day, publicly guess up to 5 players' characters. That night, you learn how many you got correct.",
    "clocktower.role.sage.desc": "If the Demon kills you, you learn that it is 1 of 2 players.",
    "clocktower.role.grandmother.desc": "You start knowing a good player & their character. If the Demon kills them, you die too.",
    "clocktower.role.sailor.desc": "Each night, choose an alive player: either you or they are drunk until dusk. You can't die.",
    "clocktower.role.chambermaid.desc": "Each night, choose 2 alive players (not yourself): you learn how many woke tonight due to their ability.",
    "clocktower.role.exorcist.desc": "Each night*, choose a player (different to last night): the Demon, if chosen, learns who you are then doesn't wake tonight.",
    "clocktower.role.innkeeper.desc": "Each night*, choose 2 players: they can't die tonight, but 1 is drunk until dusk.",
    "clocktower.role.gambler.desc": "Each night*, choose a player & guess their character: if you guess wrong, you die.",
    "clocktower.role.gossip.desc": "Each day, you may make a public statement. Tonight, if it was true, a player dies.",
    "clocktower.role.courtier.desc": "Once per game, at night, choose a character: they are drunk for 3 nights & 3 days.",
    "clocktower.role.professor.desc": "Once per game, at night*, choose a dead player: if they are a Townsfolk, they are resurrected.",
    "clocktower.role.minstrel.desc": "When a Minion dies by execution, all other players (except Travellers) are drunk until dusk tomorrow.",
    "clocktower.role.tealady.desc": "If both your alive neighbors are good, they can't die.",
    "clocktower.role.pacifist.desc": "Executed good players might not die.",
    "clocktower.role.fool.desc": "The 1st time you die, you don't.",
    "clocktower.role.acrobat.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: if they are or become drunk or poisoned tonight, you die.",
    "clocktower.role.alchemist.desc": "You have a minion ability. When using this, the Storyteller may prompt you to choose differently.",
    "clocktower.role.alsaahir.desc": "Each day, if you publicly guess which players are Minion(s) and Demon(s), good wins.",
    "clocktower.role.amnesiac.desc": "You do not know what your ability is. Each day, privately guess what it is: you learn how accurate you are.",
    "clocktower.role.atheist.desc": "The Storyteller can break the game rules, and if executed, good wins, even if you are dead. §7[No §7evil §7characters]§r",
    "clocktower.role.balloonist.desc": "Each night, you learn a player of a different character type than last night. §7[+0 §7or §7+1 §7Outsider]§r",
    "clocktower.role.banshee.desc": "If the Demon kills you, all players learn this. From now on, you may nominate twice per day and vote twice per nomination.",
    "clocktower.role.bountyhunter.desc": "You start knowing 1 evil player. If the player you know dies, you learn another evil player tonight. §7[+1 §7Townsfolk §7is §7evil.]§r",
    "clocktower.role.cannibal.desc": "You have the ability of the recently killed executee. If they are evil, you are poisoned until a good player dies by execution.",
    "clocktower.role.choirboy.desc": "If the Demon kills the King, you learn which player is the Demon. §7[+the §7King]§r",
    "clocktower.role.cultleader.desc": "Each night, you become the alignment of an alive neighbor. If all good players choose to join your cult, your team wins.",
    "clocktower.role.engineer.desc": "Once per game, at night, choose which Minions or which Demon is in play.",
    "clocktower.role.farmer.desc": "When you die at night, an alive good player becomes a Farmer.",
    "clocktower.role.fisherman.desc": "Once per game, during the day, visit the Storyteller for some advice to help your team win.",
    "clocktower.role.general.desc": "Each night, you learn which alignment the Storyteller believes is winning: good, evil, or neither.",
    "clocktower.role.highpriestess.desc": "Each night, learn which player the Storyteller believes you should talk to most.",
    "clocktower.role.huntsman.desc": "Once per game, at night, choose a living player: the Damsel, if chosen, becomes a not-in-play Townsfolk. §7[+the §7Damsel]§r",
    "clocktower.role.king.desc": "Each night, if the dead equal or outnumber the living, you learn 1 alive character. The Demon knows you are the King.",
    "clocktower.role.knight.desc": "You start knowing 2 players that are not the Demon.",
    "clocktower.role.lycanthrope.desc": "Each night*, choose an alive player. If good, they die & the Demon doesn't kill tonight. One good player registers as evil.",
    "clocktower.role.magician.desc": "The Demon thinks you are a Minion. Minions think you are a Demon.",
    "clocktower.role.nightwatchman.desc": "Once per game, at night, choose a player: they learn that you are the Nightwatchman.",
    "clocktower.role.noble.desc": "You start knowing 3 players, 1 and only 1 of which is evil.",
    "clocktower.role.pixie.desc": "You start knowing 1 in-play Townsfolk. If you were mad that you were this character, you gain their ability when they die.",
    "clocktower.role.poppygrower.desc": "Minions & Demons do not know each other. If you die, they learn who each other are that night.",
    "clocktower.role.princess.desc": "On your 1st day, if you nominated & executed a player, the Demon doesn't kill tonight.",
    "clocktower.role.preacher.desc": "Each night, choose a player: a Minion, if chosen, learns this. All chosen Minions have no ability.",
    "clocktower.role.shugenja.desc": "You start knowing if your closest evil player is clockwise or anti-clockwise. If equidistant, this info is arbitrary.",
    "clocktower.role.steward.desc": "You start knowing 1 good player.",
    "clocktower.role.villageidiot.desc": "Each night, choose a player: you learn their alignment. §7[+0 §7to §7+2 §7Village §7Idiots. §71 §7of §7the §7extras §7is §7drunk]§r",
    "clocktower.role.butler.desc": "Each night, choose a player (not yourself): tomorrow, you may only vote if they are voting too.",
    "clocktower.role.saint.desc": "If you die by execution, your team loses.",
    "clocktower.role.recluse.desc": "You might register as evil & as a Minion or Demon, even if dead.",
    "clocktower.role.drunk.desc": "You do not know you are the Drunk. You think you are a Townsfolk character, but you are not.",
    "clocktower.role.mutant.desc": "If you are \"mad\" about being an Outsider, you might be executed.",
    "clocktower.role.sweetheart.desc": "When you die, 1 player is drunk from now on.",
    "clocktower.role.barber.desc": "If you died today or tonight, the Demon may choose 2 players (not another Demon) to swap characters.",
    "clocktower.role.klutz.desc": "When you learn that you died, publicly choose 1 alive player: if they are evil, your team loses.",
    "clocktower.role.goon.desc": "Each night, the 1st player to choose you with their ability is drunk until Dusk. You become their alignment.",
    "clocktower.role.lunatic.desc": "You think you are a Demon, but you are not. The Demon knows who you are & who you choose at night.",
    "clocktower.role.tinker.desc": "You might die at any time.",
    "clocktower.role.moonchild.desc": "When you learn that you died, publicly choose 1 alive player. Tonight, if it was a good player, they die.",
    "clocktower.role.damsel.desc": "All Minions know a Damsel is in play. If a Minion publicly guesses you (once), your team loses.",
    "clocktower.role.golem.desc": "You may only nominate once per game. When you do, if the nominee is not the Demon, they die.",
    "clocktower.role.hatter.desc": "If you died today or tonight, the Minion & Demon players may choose new Minion & Demon characters to be.",
    "clocktower.role.hermit.desc": "You have all Outsider abilities. §7[-0 §7or §7-1 §7Outsider]§r",
    "clocktower.role.heretic.desc": "Whoever wins, loses & whoever loses, wins even if you are dead.",
    "clocktower.role.ogre.desc": "On your 1st night, choose a player (not yourself): you become their alignment (you don't know which) even if drunk or poisoned.",
    "clocktower.role.plaguedoctor.desc": "When you die, the Storyteller gains a Minion ability.",
    "clocktower.role.politician.desc": "If you were the player most responsible for your team losing, you change alignment & win, even if dead.",
    "clocktower.role.puzzlemaster.desc": "1 player is drunk, even if you die. If you guess (once) who it is, learn the Demon player, but guess wrong & get false info.",
    "clocktower.role.snitch.desc": "Each Minion gets 3 bluffs.",
    "clocktower.role.zealot.desc": "If there are 5 or more players alive, you must vote for every nomination.",
    "clocktower.role.poisoner.desc": "Each night, choose a player: they are poisoned tonight and tomorrow day.",
    "clocktower.role.spy.desc": "Each night, you see the Grimoire. You might register as good & as a Townsfolk or Outsider, even if dead.",
    "clocktower.role.baron.desc": "There are extra Outsiders in play. §7[+2 §7Outsiders]§r",
    "clocktower.role.scarletwoman.desc": "If there are 5 or more players alive & the Demon dies, you become the Demon.",
    "clocktower.role.eviltwin.desc": "You & an opposing player know each other. If the good player is executed, evil wins. Good can't win if you both live.",
    "clocktower.role.witch.desc": "Each night, choose a player: if they nominate tomorrow, they die. If just 3 players live, you lose this ability.",
    "clocktower.role.cerenovus.desc": "Each night, choose a player & a good character: they are \"mad\" they are this character tomorrow, or they might be executed.",
    "clocktower.role.pithag.desc": "Each night*, choose a player & a character they become (if not in play). If a Demon is made, deaths tonight are arbitrary.",
    "clocktower.role.godfather.desc": "You start knowing which Outsiders are in play. If 1 died today, choose a player tonight: they die. §7[§7-1 §7or §7+1 §7Outsider]§r",
    "clocktower.role.devilsadvocate.desc": "Each night, choose a living player (different to last night): if executed tomorrow, they don't die.",
    "clocktower.role.assassin.desc": "Once per game, at night*, choose a player: they die, even if for some reason they could not.",
    "clocktower.role.mastermind.desc": "If the Demon dies by execution (ending the game), play for 1 more day. If a player is then executed, their team loses.",
    "clocktower.role.boffin.desc": "The Demon (even if drunk or poisoned) has a not-in-play good character's ability. You both know which.",
    "clocktower.role.boomdandy.desc": "If you are executed, all but 3 players die. After a 10 to 1 countdown, the player with the most players pointing at them, dies.",
    "clocktower.role.fearmonger.desc": "Each night, choose a player: if you nominate & execute them, their team loses. All players know if you choose a new player.",
    "clocktower.role.goblin.desc": "If you publicly claim to be the Goblin when nominated & are executed that day, your team wins.",
    "clocktower.role.harpy.desc": "Each night, choose 2 players: tomorrow, the 1st player is mad that the 2nd is evil, or one or both might die.",
    "clocktower.role.marionette.desc": "You think you are a good character but you are not. The Demon knows who you are. §7[You §7neighbor §7the §7Demon]§r",
    "clocktower.role.mezepheles.desc": "You start knowing a secret word. The 1st good player to say this word becomes evil that night.",
    "clocktower.role.organgrinder.desc": "All players keep their eyes closed when voting and the vote tally is secret. Each night, choose if you are drunk until dusk.",
    "clocktower.role.psychopath.desc": "Each day, before nominations, you may publicly choose a player: they die. If executed, you only die if you lose roshambo.",
    "clocktower.role.summoner.desc": "You get 3 bluffs. On the 3rd night, choose a player: they become an evil Demon of your choice. §7[No §7Demon]§r",
    "clocktower.role.vizier.desc": "All players know you are the Vizier. You cannot die during the day. If good voted, you may choose to execute immediately.",
    "clocktower.role.widow.desc": "On your 1st night, look at the Grimoire & choose a player: they are poisoned. 1 good player knows a Widow is in play.",
    "clocktower.role.wizard.desc": "Once per game, choose to make a wish. If granted, it might have a price & leave a clue as to its nature.",
    "clocktower.role.xaan.desc": "On night X, all Townsfolk are poisoned until dusk. §7[X §7Outsiders]§r",
    "clocktower.role.imp.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. If you kill yourself this way, a Minion becomes the Imp.",
    "clocktower.role.fanggu.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. The 1st Outsider this kills becomes an evil Fang Gu & you die instead. §7[+1 §7Outsider]§r",
    "clocktower.role.vigormortis.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. Minions you kill keep their ability & poison 1 Townsfolk neighbor. §7[-1 §7Outsider]§r",
    "clocktower.role.nodashii.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. Your 2 Townsfolk neighbors are poisoned.",
    "clocktower.role.vortox.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. Townsfolk abilities yield false info. Each day, if no-one is executed, evil wins.",
    "clocktower.role.zombuul.desc": "Each night*, if no-one died today, choose a player: they die. The 1st time you die, you live but register as dead.",
    "clocktower.role.pukka.desc": "Each night, choose a player: they are poisoned. The previously poisoned player dies then becomes healthy.",
    "clocktower.role.shabaloth.desc": "Each night*, choose 2 players: they die. A dead player you chose last night might be regurgitated.",
    "clocktower.role.po.desc": "Each night*, you may choose a player: they die. If your last choice was no-one, choose 3 players tonight.",
    "clocktower.role.alhadikhia.desc": "Each night*, you may choose 3 players (all players learn who): each silently chooses to live or die, but if all live, all die.",
    "clocktower.role.kazali.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. §7[You §7choose §7which §7players §7are §7which §7Minions. §7-? §7to §7+? §7Outsiders]",
    "clocktower.role.legion.desc": "Each night*, a player might die. Executions fail if only evil voted. You register as a Minion too. §7[Most §7players §7are §7Legion]§r",
    "clocktower.role.leviathan.desc": "If more than 1 good player is executed, evil wins. All players know you are in play. After day 5, evil wins.",
    "clocktower.role.lilmonsta.desc": "Each night, Minions choose who babysits Lil' Monsta & \"is the Demon\". Each night*, a player might die. §7[+1 §7Minion]§r",
    "clocktower.role.lleech.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. You start by choosing a player: they are poisoned. You die if & only if they are dead.",
    "clocktower.role.lordoftyphon.desc": "Each night*, choose a player: they die. §7[Evil §7characters §7are §7in §7a §7line. §7You §7are §7in §7the §7middle. §7+1 §7Minion. §7-? §7to §7+? §7Outsiders]§r",
    "clocktower.role.ojo.desc": "Each night*, choose a character: they die. If they are not in play, the Storyteller chooses who dies.",
    "clocktower.role.riot.desc": "On day 3, Minions become Riot & nominees die but nominate an alive player immediately. This must happen.",
    "clocktower.role.yaggababble.desc": "You start knowing a secret phrase. For each time you said it publicly today, a player might die.",
