    "clocktower.role.doomsayer.desc": "If 4 or more players live, each living player may publicly choose (once per game) that a player of their own alignment dies.",
    "clocktower.role.angel.desc": "Something bad might happen to whoever is most responsible for the death of a new player.",
    "clocktower.role.buddhist.desc": "For the first 2 minutes of each day, veteran players may not talk.",
    "clocktower.role.hellslibrarian.desc": "Something bad might happen to whoever talks when the Storyteller has asked for silence.",
    "clocktower.role.revolutionary.desc": "2 neighboring players are known to be the same alignment. Once per game, 1 of them registers falsely.",
    "clocktower.role.fiddler.desc": "Once per game, the Demon secretly chooses an opposing player: all players choose which of these 2 players win.",
    "clocktower.role.toymaker.desc": "The Demon may choose not to attack & must do this at least once per game. Evil players get normal starting info.",
    "clocktower.role.fibbin.desc": "Once per game, 1 good player might get incorrect information.",
    "clocktower.role.duchess.desc": "Each day, 3 players may choose to visit you. At night*, each visitor learns how many visitors are evil, but 1 gets false info.",
    "clocktower.role.sentinel.desc": "There might be 1 extra or 1 fewer Outisder in play.",
    "clocktower.role.spiritofivory.desc": "There can't be more than 1 extra evil player.",
    "clocktower.role.djinn.desc": "Use the Djinn's special rule. All players know what it is.",
    "clocktower.role.bootlegger.desc": "This script has homebrew characters or rules.",
    "clocktower.role.deusexfiasco.desc": "At least once per game, the Storyteller will make a mistake, correct it, and publicly admit to it.",
    "clocktower.role.ferryman.desc": "On the final day, all dead players regain their vote token.",
    "clocktower.role.gardener.desc": "The Storyteller assigns 1 or more players' characters.",
    "clocktower.role.stormcatcher.desc": "Name a good character. If in play, they can only die by execution, but evil players learn which player it is.",
    "clocktower.role.bigwig.desc": "Each nominee chooses a player: until voting, only they may speak & they are mad the nominee is good or they might die.",
    "clocktower.role.godofug.desc": "One Ug hat. When wear Ug hat, must speak one sound at a time but vote twice. If fail, pass Ug hat.",
    "clocktower.role.hindu.desc": "The first 4 players to die are immediately reincarnated as Travellers of the same alignment.",
    "clocktower.role.knaves.desc": "There are 2 Storytellers: one lies & one tells the truth. Once per game, at dusk, they might switch.",
    "clocktower.role.pope.desc": "There are duplicate good characters in play. They might also be bluffs.",
    "clocktower.role.tor.desc": "Players don't know their character or alignment. They learn them when they die.",
    "clocktower.role.ventriloquist.desc": "If a player is mad as a fresh character during their nomination, they might not die if executed today.",
    "clocktower.role.zenomancer.desc": "One or more players each have a goal. When achieved, that player learns a piece of true info.",
